article.description: — Frankie Fidler scored 23 points as Omaha beat South Dakota 91-84 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Fidler's 23 help Omaha beat South Dakota 91-84
article.linkText: Fidler's 23 help Omaha beat South Dakota 91-84
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- — Frankie Fidler scored 23 points as Omaha beat South Dakota 91-84 on Thursday night. Fidler also contributed six rebounds and six assists for the Mavericks (13-14, 6-6 Summit League). JJ White scored 18 points while shooting 7 for 10, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc. Marquel Sutton had 14 points and was 5 of 10 shooting and 4 of 8 from the free throw line. Bostyn Holt led the Coyotes (10-16, 3-8) in scoring, finishing with 22 points. Lahat Thioune added 20 points and six rebounds for South Dakota. In addition, Kaleb Stewart finished with 18 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
